HLENGANI Ngwenyana (53) sold his white Toyota Corolla two years ago.But last week, the buyer returned the car saying he wanted his money back because the car had a ghost.Hlengani, from KwaThema, Ekurhuleni told the buyer he didn’t have the money and resold the car to another person to pay the buyer. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>But the buyer refused to take the R20 000 last Saturday and allegedly shot him dead at his house instead!Kwa-Thema Police Captain Thabo Sibuyi said Hlengani was shot 15 times in his right leg and body. “His right leg was fractured from the impact of the bullets. He was certified dead at the scene by paramedics. A case of murder has been opened,” he said.Sibuyi said cops are looking for two suspects who fled on foot.Hlengani’s wife, Nobuhle Mbatha, said when her husband sold the car it was in good condition. She said there were no ghosts as the buyer claimed. “We appeal to anyone who has information to help nab these suspects to come forward.“Anyone who has information that could help the police nab the suspects, should phone CrimeStop on 08600 10111.”